name: Floating city - diaries of a nighter
description: "Luckily there is the Night. What is outside of us during the day takes place in us during the night." (Helene Cixous, Stigmata, Routledge 2005 p.60)  I wander at nights - inside and outside. It stretches like a field of potential of many unmarked, uninterrupted hours before me. That which is solid by day becomes fluid at night and that which is unseen in light becomes visible in shadows. I feel like the city itself detaches from earth and we float together to new spaces, growing different roots
